bug.short_desc: Opera 10 have problem with Options from SelectBox in Scroll area

long_desc.thetext: They are mispositioned. It seems that to Y position of options popup added scrollY twice.
Opera/9.80 (Windows NT 5.1; U; en) Presto/2.2.15 Version/10.00
Hi, could you provide a code sample and/or a screenshot, please? Have you seen this in a stable Opera release (like 9.64) as well?

To recap: this bug applies only to Opera 10, which is currently available as a RC, close to a final release.
Johnny, please try to figure out if this is an issue in the browser or the framework. AFAIK Martin worked on the Location implementation recently, so he might have valuable input (or likes to take care of the bug).
If it is likely that the browser keeps changing here (i.e. the current behavior isn't documented), we could afford to wait for 10 final.
I will create a test case and check this issue.
